This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 1, 2014, as Loyalty Day. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the founding ideals of the United States, such as liberty, equality, and justice. It highlights that loyalty in America is not defined by allegiance to a single leader or political party, but rather by a commitment to shared values and the well-being of the nation. The proclamation encourages Americans to reaffirm their allegiance to the United States and pay tribute to the country's heritage of freedom.